<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1296] Bulk upload can overwhelm a datanode filling its disk because HDFS deletes lag</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1296</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From a private mail with J&#233;r&#244;me Thi&#232;vre:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Two times I got the same kind of problems described by schubert zhang in the thread *HDFS unbalance issue. (HBase over HDFS). *The first time, I found one of my regionserver  with a full disk, whereas the others were at 10% of their capacity. I saw a lot of move file command at hadoop level from the full regionserver to others, but after check on the hdfs, I can see that hadoop copies the file but fails to delete it.  As the regionserver disk was full, it didn&apos;t work anymore, even after hadoop and hbase restart. I had to delete all the data.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;The second time this problem occurs I stopped the row insertion process before the disk was full. After hadoop and hbase restart, hadoop has deleted the files and the system was operational.&lt;br/&gt;
It seems that in some cases where the system is heavily loaded with continuous writes and compactions, hadoop can&apos;t remove files.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
